<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >
Custom Summary Demo
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Essential Grouping supports custom counters and custom summaries which derives summary information from custom collection logic. </Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\sample.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >
Features
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph >
Essential Grouping lets users to add one or more summary items to each group. Each summary item automatically reflects changes made to data items. Because of the highly optimized, balanced tree structures used in the grouping engine, the calculation of summary values is very fast.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >
Interactive Features
</Paragraph>
<List Margin="25,0,0,0"><ListItem><Paragraph xml:space="preserve">In this sample, the last two fields show custom counters. One counter automatically counts the quantity of all records, and the other counts the quantity of the visible records (using a filter set to [UnitPrice]> 20). Changing the quantity in one record will automatically update all subsequent records.</Paragraph></ListItem></List>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0"><ListItem><Paragraph xml:space="preserve">This example also shows custom summaries. A simple custom summary counts the total value; a more advanced summary class creates a vector of values that are in memory and performs statistical functions.</Paragraph></ListItem></List>


